text: Code named ‘The November Man’, Peter Devereaux (Pierce Brosnan) is a lethal and highly trained ex-CIA agent, who has been enjoying a quiet life in Switzerland. When Devereaux is lured out of retirement for one last mission, he must protect valuable witness, Alice Fournier, (Olga Kurylenko).He soon uncovers this assignment marks him a target of his former friend and CIA protégé David Mason (Luke Bracey). With growing suspicions of a mole in the agency, there is no one Devereaux can trust, no rules and no holds barred.  With a screenplay by Michael Finch & Karl Gajdusek based on Bill Granger’s novel “There are No Spies” from the bestselling November Man book series, THE NOVEMBER MAN is the ultimate cat and mouse game set in the world of international espionage. Directed by Roger Donaldson (The Bank Job, No Way Out, Thirteen Days), the film is produced by Beau St. Clair of Irish DreamTime and Sriram Das of Das Films.

text: Pay no heed to the plethora of dimwits, who can't distinguish as much as differentiate their ass from their elbow, what constitutes a quality movie, how this got such low ratings is beyond me other than the explanation I just gave, Great cast, great acting, great plot, great action, keeps you guessing, good twists, layered story arc with complex multi layered conflicting character motivations, commentary on conspiracy among governments and war crimes, its got it all, on par with a bourne movie if not better, good to see Pierce back in action and he kicks ass with aplomb, he is like the antibond, not the over the top action ladies man, he says to his Co agent in training who after kisses a girl, "If you want a relationship, get a dog" ... Classic, a gritty, yet still charming, pragmatic and professional, ... Baller, a damn fine movie
